LAGOS  – Green Africa, the Lagos-based value airline has appointed Mr. Obiukwu Mbanuzuo as its Chief Commercial Officer (CCO) and a member of the company’s senior leadership team effective. A statement by Oyindamola Fashogbon, the Brand Marketing Specialist, Green Africa said that his appointment took effect from this March 2022. The statement hinted that Mbanuzuo is an industry veteran with two decades of global industry experience and a unique understanding of the Nigerian and African markets. Prior to his appointment, Mbanuzuo was the Chief Operating Officer (COO), CCO and Accountable Manager of Dana Airlines where he provided overall leadership for the day-to-day management of the company and was the airline’s officer responsible to the Nigerian Civil Aviation Authority (NCAA). He was in that position with Dana Air for almost a decade. Babawande Afolabi, Founder, Green Africa said the airline was delighted to welcome Mbanuzuo to the airline. According to Afolabi, Mbanuzuo’s track record, depth of commercial aviation knowledge and experience across various markets made him an ideal senior leader to steer Green Africa to commercial success as the company scales. Mbanuzuo commenced his aviation career at Virgin Atlantic where he served as a member of the revenue management and network planning team. He was later seconded to Nigeria to help get Virgin Nigeria off the ground and build the commercial team. POLL Speaking on his appointment, Mbanuzuo said: “I believe Green Africa has a great business model and a qualified team across disciplines to positively impact aviation and air travel in Nigeria.”